2452			; the core word dictionary v4 
2452			; https://www.complang.tuwien.ac.at/forth/gforth/Docs-html/Notation.html#Notation 
2452			 
2452			; this is a linked list for each of the system words used 
2452			; user defined words will follow the same format but will be in ram 
2452			 
2452			 
2452			; 
2452			; 
2452			; define linked list: 
2452			; 
2452			; 1. compiled byte op code 
2452			; 2. len of text word 
2452			; 3. text word 
2452			; 4. ptr to next dictionary word 
2452			; 5. asm, calls etc for the word 
2452			; 
2452			;  if 1 == 0 then last word in dict  
2452			;   
2452			; set the start of dictionary scanning to be in ram and the last word point to the system dict 
2452			;  
2452			;  
2452			; create basic standard set of words 
2452			; 
2452			;  
2452			; + - / * DUP EMIT . SWAP IF..THEN..ELSE DO..LOOP  : ; DROP  
2452			; 2DUP 2DROP 2SWAP  
2452			; @ C@ - get byte  
2452			; ! C! - store byte 
2452			; 0< true if less than zero 
2452			; 0= true if zero 
2452			; < >  
2452			; = true if same 
2452			; variables 
2452			 
2452			 
2452			; Hardware specific words I may need 
2452			; 
2452			; IN OUT  
2452			; calls to key util functions 
2452			; calls to hardward abstraction stuff 
2452			; easy control of frame buffers and lcd i/o 
2452			; keyboard  
2452			 
2452			 
2452			;DICT: macro 
2452			; op_code, len, word, next 
2452			;    word: 
2452			;    db op_code 
2452			;    ds word zero term 
2452			;    dw next 
2452			;    endm 
2452			 
2452			 
2452			 
2452			 
